                </article>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3>Goo Technologies â€”</h3>

                <article class="grid-1-4">
                    <time>2014 â€” 2015</time>

                    <div>
                        <h4>UI/UX Designer</h4>
                        <h5>24 000 SEK/month</h5>

                        <p>
                            My good friend <b>Hugo Campos</b> (with whom I worked at WannaPlayer) and I both joined this super exciting gaming adjacent startup, working on a WebGL engine and editor that allowed you to have games and other 3D experience running on any browser (very similar to <a href="https://spline.design/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spline</a>).
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            This salary meant a 3.4x increase from what I made back in Lisbon. In hindsight, it was a low salary by Swedish standards, but everyone there was trading money to work in something we all deeply believed in.
