                        <p>
                            Even with a cut salary, I worked my but off from day one. One week after starting, I got praised by the CEO during our town hall for helping to release the new website. During a hackathon, I prototyped a voice search feature that sales used to secure one of our largest customers.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            Then <b>COVID-19</b> happened, and because in Sweden, the last employees hired needed to be the first out in a layoff, I was again between jobs (a local euphemism for being unemployed). And no, I did not get to keep any stock options I had already worked towards.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </article>
